    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Type of bobbin lace made in Paris from the 18th century onwards. This firm lace, not fit for gathering, is characterized by its hexagonal mesh, which is formed by intertwining triangles. The pattern consists mostly of flowers, leaves or vines or occasionally animal figures.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
